---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout title="Ledgr — Privacy Policy" description="Ledgr privacy policy. How Ledgr handles budget data, AI messages, receipts, and subscriptions.">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-[#0b0f17] text-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 py-16">
      <a href="/ledgr" class="text-white/35 hover:text-white text-sm transition mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-1">
        ← Back to Ledgr
      </a>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-6 mb-2">Privacy Policy — Ledgr</h1>
      <p class="text-white/35 mb-10">Last updated: May 5, 2026</p>

      <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Ledgr is a personal budgeting app developed by Justin Bundrick. This policy explains what data Ledgr uses, where it is stored, and how cloud AI features work.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Data Stored On Your Device</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Ledgr stores the financial information you choose to enter on your device, including:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/60 mb-6 space-y-2 leading-relaxed">
        <li>Transactions, amounts, merchants, notes, categories, and dates</li>
        <li>Budgets, bills, subscriptions, income sources, and savings goals</li>
        <li>Receipt images you choose to attach</li>
        <li>Freelancer mode business/personal tags and tax set-aside settings</li>
        <li>App preferences such as currency, app lock, and display settings</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Sign In with Apple</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Some cloud features may require Sign in with Apple so Ledgr can create a secure session for AI and receipt scanning requests. Apple may provide a private user identifier and, if you allow it, an email relay address. Ledgr uses this only to authenticate cloud feature access.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">AI Assistant</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        When you use Ledgr's AI assistant, your message and relevant budget context may be sent securely over HTTPS to Ledgr's cloud service so a response can be generated. Relevant context can include recent transactions, budget categories, bills, goals, totals, and preferences needed to answer the request. Ledgr does not sell this data or use it for advertising.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Receipt Scanning</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        When you scan a receipt or financial document, the selected image is sent securely to Ledgr's cloud OCR service so transaction details can be extracted. Receipt images attached to transactions remain in your app data unless you delete them.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Bank Connections</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Ledgr does not connect to bank accounts and does not ask for bank usernames, passwords, or account credentials.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Camera, Photos, Microphone, and Speech</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Ledgr may request camera or photo library access for receipt scanning, microphone access for voice input, and speech recognition for voice expense logging. These permissions are used only for the feature you choose to use and can be changed in iOS Settings.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Notifications</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Ledgr may request notification permission for reminders such as bills, weekly briefings, and planning prompts. Notifications can be disabled in iOS Settings.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Subscriptions</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Ledgr Pro subscriptions are processed by Apple through the App Store. Ledgr does not receive or store your payment card information. You can manage or cancel subscriptions in your Apple ID settings.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">What We Do Not Do</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/60 mb-6 space-y-2 leading-relaxed">
        <li>We do not sell your personal or financial data</li>
        <li>We do not display third-party ads</li>
        <li>We do not request bank credentials</li>
        <li>We do not track your precise location</li>
        <li>We do not use your data for credit decisions, lending, or financial advice</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Ledgr is not intended for children under 13 and does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        This policy may be updated from time to time. Updates will appear on this page with a revised date.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Questions? Email <a href="mailto:bunjistudios@gmail.com" class="text-amber-300 hover:text-amber-200 underline">bunjistudios@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>

      <footer class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-white/10 text-white/35 text-sm">
        <p>© 2026 Justin Bundrick. All rights reserved.</p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
